* Use canonical 6502 assembly conventions for the Kick Assembly

* Keep source files small and targetted to specific functionality

* Leverage the C64/C128 KERNAL routines, but do not use any of the BASIC
  routines once the main program runs

* Because we are not using BASIC after the initial loader, the assembly program
  can freely use any of the zero page space dedicated to BASIC as needed, but
  the program should be able to exit cleanly and return to BASIC if possible

* Leverage the KickAss.Unit unit testing framework and always add unit testing
  for every feature

* Use vice --console for any automated testing as needde

* Always refer to ARCHITECTURE.md for overall design and architecutre.

* Always refer to README.md for overall program feature set and goal.

